## Summary of Billboard Hot 100 Chart Article

**Source:** Billboard  
**Date:** January 02, 2013  
**Author:** tolsen

### Key Facts and Statistics:

This article presents the Billboard Hot 100 chart for a specific week. The chart lists songs ranked 1-96 with detailed performance metrics including:

- Current position
- Last week's position (LW)
- Peak position
- Weeks on chart
- Artist credits, songwriters, and producers
- Record labels

### Notable Chart Positions (Top 20):

1. **"DTMF"** - Bad Bunny (Peak: #1, 22 weeks on chart)
2. **"Baile Inolvidable"** - Bad Bunny (Peak: #2, 22 weeks)
3. **"Man I Need"** - Olivia Dean (Peak: #2, 25 weeks)
4. **"Choosin'"** - Texas Ella Langley (Peak: #1, 17 weeks)
5. **"Nuevayol"** - Bad Bunny (Peak: #5, 22 weeks)
6. **"Ordinary"** - Alex Warren (Peak: #1, 52 weeks)
7. **"Titi Me Pregunto"** - Bad Bunny (Re-entry, Peak: #5, 31 weeks)
8. **"Opalite"** - Taylor Swift (Peak: #2, 19 weeks)
9. **"Golden"** - HUNTR/X: EJAE, Audrey Nuna & REI AMI (Peak: #1, 34 weeks)
10. **"I Just Might"** - Bruno Mars (Peak: #1, 5 weeks)

The chart continues through position 96, featuring multiple artists including J. Cole (with several new entries from what appears to be an album release), Don Toliver, Luke Combs, and others.

### Observations:

- Bad Bunny dominates the chart with multiple entries throughout the top 100
- Several J. Cole tracks appear as "NEW" entries, suggesting a recent album release
- The chart includes detailed production and songwriting credits for each entry
- Multiple re-entries are noted, particularly for Bad Bunny tracks

**Note:** There is no mention of AI-created songs or AI involvement in any of the charting tracks based on the credits and information provided in this chart listing.

<QuestionSource url="https://www.billboard.com/lists/ai-artists-on-billboard-charts/childpets-galore/">
# Summary of Billboard Article on AI Artists Charting

**Key Facts and Statistics:**

- As of November 2025, at least six AI or AI-assisted artists have debuted on various Billboard charts in recent months
- The actual figure could be higher due to difficulty in identifying AI-generated content
- At least one AI artist has debuted in each of the past six chart weeks (as of the article date), suggesting the trend is "quickly accelerating"

**Notable AI Artist Examples:**

1. **Xania Monet** (most prominent example):
   - Created by Mississippi-based songwriter Telisha "Nikki" Jones using Suno AI platform
   - Jones writes ~90% of lyrics herself
   - Debuted on multiple charts in September 2025: Hot Gospel Songs with "Let Go, Let Go" (peaked at No. 3) and Hot R&B Songs with "How Was I Supposed to Know?" (No. 20 peak)
   - First known AI artist to debut on a Billboard radio chart (No. 30 on Adult R&B Airplay chart dated Nov. 11)
   - Signed to Hallwood Media for a multimillion-dollar deal after a bidding war with offers reaching $3 million
   - Catalog has amassed 44.4 million official U.S. streams
   - Five songs generated an estimated $52,000 in just over two months

2. **Other charting AI artists** (with stream counts):
   - Child Pets Galore: 1.2 million U.S. streams
   - Unbound Music: 5.5 million streams
   - Enlly Blue: 5.3 million streams
   - Juno Skye: 1.6 million streams
   - Breaking Rust: 1.6 million streams

**Detection Methods:**
- Some artists self-identify as AI on DSP artist pages
- Billboard cross-checked songs using Deezer's AI detection tool, which flags AI-generated content

**Historical Context:**
- AI artists appeared on Billboard charts as early as 2023 (Trump The Don and BOI WHAT)

**Note:** All charting mentioned in this article are on various Billboard charts, but **none** are on the Billboard Hot 100 specifically, which is the focus of the underlying Metaculus question.
